OL,3,CDo rising temperatures mean rising
OL,4,Cdeaths?
OL,6,FHeat health warnings - issued by
OL,7,Fpublic health officials - tell the
OL,8,Fpopulation that rising temperatures
OL,9,Fcould pose a risk to those who are
OL,10,Fvulnerable.
OL,12,FSome may brand this the 'nanny state'
OL,13,Fbut the data speaks for itself.
OL,15,FAccording to the World Health
OL,16,FOrganisation, there are 176,000 heat-
OL,17,Frelated deaths each year in Europe. As
OL,18,Fa result of climate change they say
OL,19,Fthe number of over 65s dying from heat
OL,20,Fhas increased by 85% this century.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
