OL,3,CDo rising temperatures mean rising
OL,4,Cdeaths?
OL,6,F"The risk of heat with the body is
OL,7,Fthat the core body temperature gets
OL,8,Ftoo high. Normal core body temperature
OL,9,Fis about 37 degrees. Once we start
OL,10,Fpushing that up above 38 and towards
OL,11,F39 and 40, we start to get into
OL,12,Fdifficulty," James Barber of The
OL,13,FAltitude Centre tells me.
OL,15,FAnd if you're elderly or vulnerable,
OL,16,Fit's particularly dangerous.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
